## Lifecycle State Machine

```
┌──────────┐    ┌───────────┐    ┌──────────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────┐    ┌──────────┐    ┌───────┐
│ Detected │───▶│ Contained │───▶│ Root Cause Identified │───▶│ Actions Implemented │───▶│ Verified │───▶│ Closed│
└──────────┘    └───────────┘    └──────────────────────┘    └─────────────────────┘    └──────────┘    └───────┘
                     │                          │                          │
                     │                          │                          │
                     └──────────────────────────┴──────────────────────────┘
                                             │
                                             ▼
                                         ┌──────────┐
                                         │ Reopened │
                                         └──────────┘
```

**Transitions:**
- **Detected → Contained**: Immediate containment steps confirmed
- **Contained → Root Cause Identified**: RCA document approved
- **Root Cause Identified → Actions Implemented**: All corrective and preventive actions deployed
- **Actions Implemented → Verified**: Post-deployment validation passed
- **Verified → Closed**: CAPA peer-reviewed and archived
- **Any state → Reopened**: New evidence discovered or verification failed

## Minimal REST API

```javascript
// POST /api/v1/capas - Create CAPA
app.post('/api/v1/capas', async (req, res) => {
  const { tenant_id, incident_id, issue_type, evidence } = req.body;
  const capa = await db.capas.create({
    id: uuid(),
    tenant_id,
    incident_id,
    issue_type,
    evidence: evidence.map(e => ({ ...e, uploaded_at: new Date() })),
    status: 'detected',
    created_at: new Date(),
    updated_at: new Date()
  });
  await emit('capa_created', capa);
  res.status(201).json(capa);
});

// PATCH /api/v1/capas/:id - Update CAPA
app.patch('/api/v1/capas/:id', async (req, res) => {
  const { status, root_cause, corrective_action, preventive_action, evidence } = req.body;
  const capa = await db.capas.findById(req.params.id);

  validateTransition(capa.status, status);

  const updated = await db.capas.update(req.params.id, {
    ...(status && { status }),
    ...(root_cause && { root_cause }),
    ...(corrective_action && { corrective_action }),
    ...(preventive_action && { preventive_action }),
    ...(evidence && { $push: { evidence: { $each: evidence.map(e => ({ ...e, uploaded_at: new Date() })) } } }),
    updated_at: new Date()
  });

  if (status === 'verified') {
    await emit('capa_verified', updated);
  }
  res.json(updated);
});

// GET /api/v1/capas/:id - Retrieve CAPA
app.get('/api/v1/capas/:id', async (req, res) => {
  res.json(await db.capas.findById(req.params.id));
});
```

